ce:section.ce:para:
The newly fabricated sensors were characterized in a ferri-/ferrocyanide redox probe using cyclic voltammetry and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy (EIS) (Figs. 5 and 6

                        , Table 2
                        ). Using the ΔEp values as well as the resistance-to-charge (RCT) values from cyclic voltammograms in Fig. 5 and the Nyquist plots in Fig. 6 (following fitting with the Randles-Sevcik circuit), the electron-transporting abilities of the probes were estimated. An estimation rather than an absolute determination was made as these observations, as stated timeously, are not a true reflection of the sensors’ electrochemical ability or potential.
